I understand that we want this to be realistic, but we could simplify considerably if we just returned the outpoints here:
```C++
static std::vector<COutPoint> CreateOutpoints() noexcept
{
    static constexpr uint32_t NUM_OUTPOINTS{100};
    std::vector<COutPoint> outpoints;
    outpoints.reserve(NUM_OUTPOINTS);

    for (const auto i : std::views::iota(uint32_t{1}, NUM_OUTPOINTS + 1)) {
        outpoints.emplace_back(Txid::FromUint256(uint256(i)), /*nIn=*/0);
    }

    return outpoints;
}
```

If you disagree, just resolve without a comment.
